# ============================================================================
#  .gitignore  --  keep build artifacts out of the repository
# ============================================================================
#  We commit SOURCE only. Everything that the compiler/linker regenerates is
#  ignored so the repo stays small and never has merge conflicts on binaries.
# ============================================================================

# --- command-line build output (build.ps1) ---
/build/

# --- Visual Studio per-user / IDE state ---
.vs/
*.user
*.suo
*.vcxproj.user

# --- Visual Studio / MSBuild output + intermediate directories ---
# Our project writes the exe to vs\<Config>\ and objects to vs\<Config>\obj\,
# and the CUDA targets stage temporaries under vs\ChaCha20CUDA\.
vs/Debug/
vs/Release/
vs/x64/
vs/ChaCha20CUDA/
**/x64/Debug/
**/x64/Release/

# --- object / binary / debug files ---
*.obj
*.o
*.exe
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.exp
*.lib
*.idb

# --- nvcc intermediate / device-code temporaries ---
*.ptx
*.cubin
*.fatbin
*.cudafe*
*.module_id
tmpxft_*
